When Chris Rock got on stage at the 2022 Oscars, he probably expected his hosting gig to go as many of his others have: a risky joke here, a pop culture reference there, a few laughs and a swift exit – simple. Of course, that was far from what happened on Sunday night. After spotting Will Smith and Jada Pinkett Smith in the crowd, the actor and comedian referred to Pinkett Smith’s shaved head by saying: ‘G.I. Jane 2, can’t wait to see it!’ Yet, Jada’s appearance isn’t due to an upcoming sequel of the 1997 army film; she has been living with alopecia since 2018. Though the comedian’s comment was meant in jest, it wasn’t received as such. Jada was clearly upset, and moments later, her husband Will walked on stage and struck Chris with an open hand before returning to his seat. From the audience, he shouted at the comedian to ‘Keep my wife’s name out your f***ing mouth’. It was a slap and a warning heard throughout the world. Despite Smith later winning his first Oscar, and a wealth of other landmark moments that occurred on the night, this has been the main discussion point from this year’s Academy Awards, and it is a shame. {"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Metro.co.uk","duration":"T52S","thumbnailUrl":"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/03/28/03/55883579-0-image-a-10_1648435249920.jpg","uploadDate":"2022-03-28T03:40:10+0100","description":"ABC tried to censor Will Smith's outburst but his lips can still be seen to mouth the words 'Keep my wife's name out of your f***ing mouth'.","contentUrl":"https://videos.metro.co.uk/video/met/2022/03/28/6201052676286727000/640x360_MP4_6201052676286727000.mp4","height":360,"width":640}  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web
